cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a model for mining multimedia data, specifically captioned images, using a combination of multivariate Poisson and Gaussian distributions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of text data in conjunction with images suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the focus on multimedia data as a whole suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
